parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lurch, hesitate, or buck, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates
lurches forward
clunks
or bucks while starting
accelerating
or coming to a stop; the vehicle shifts hard or unpredictably; the transmission downshifts with a noticeable jerk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose brake pressure, leading to increased stopping distance, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes very stiff
requiring extra effort to stop the vehicle; the brake system loses pressure
especially at low speeds; the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration issues can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially affect vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle has a horrible vibration from around 45 mph and up; the vibration is felt throughout the vehicle
making it uncomfortable to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drive train issues can cause the vehicle to clunk or vibrate, potentially affecting vehicle control and safety.
symptoms: The drive shaft clunks when stopping at a traffic light; the vehicle has major mechanical concerns
including issues with the drive train.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective lash adjustment steering box can cause excessive slop and uncontrollable, unintended steering shifts, leading to vehicle instability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Excessive play in the steering wheel
sloppy steering
vehicle veers out of lane unexpectedly
difficulty controlling the vehicle
especially in icy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause sudden loss of power, jerking, and hesitation, which can lead to accidents, especially on the highway.
symptoms: Transmission shifts erratically
hesitation when shifting
loss of power
jerking or kicking sensation
especially when driving at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear seatbelt failure can cause the seatbelt to not retract properly, which can lead to entanglement or obstruction, increasing the risk of injury or accident.
symptoms: Rear seatbelt does not retract when unbuckled
seatbelt must be manually fed back in
belt may dangle or get shut in the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle shaking and vibrations can cause loss of control, especially at high speeds, and may lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or vibrates violently
especially at high speeds
engine vibrates around 80 mph
vehicle pulls or fights when changing lanes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lane departure and drifting issues can cause accidents, especially on highways, and may lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle drifts or wanders out of lane
difficulty keeping the vehicle in lane
especially at high speeds
lane departure warning system may be triggered frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to a loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard and dead
the brake pedal loses its spongy feel
the vehicle continues to roll forward despite applying the brakes
the brakes become unresponsive after pumping the brakes a few times
the brake pedal must be pushed to the floor to stop the vehicle.
